title: Best free midi player out there.
comment: Pros: 1. Stable, only crashes if rushed, which rarely happens 2. Option to switch instruments (all 128 midi soundfont instruments that are part of the android system) 3. Option to show instruments combined on a piano stave or all the midi staves separate 4. Automatically finds any midi downloaded from the internet 5. Small app (very little download required) 6. App is not account intrusive (only uses sdcard space)   Cons(minor): 1. You have to deselect the "Combine to two staves" option every time you load a new song if you want to see all the  midi staves 2. Some of the noteheads are incomplete (missing line or tail)  Recommendations: 1. Fix the cons! 2. Label the staves in uncombined mode 3. For downloaded MIDIs, ask about quantization settings (how to interpret the MIDI to a certain detail, like in Finale) 4. Always have the play/pause button showing 5. Show what the tempo will be with the speed change (put inside or next to speed modifier)

title: Brilliant, just brilliant
comment: This app is ideal for anyone wishing to play their favourite tunes on piano, even if it wasn't originally written for it.  Find a well composed midi, and use this app to enjoy the song and generate the sheet music for it - basically it allows you to play any midi music you hear on the piano.  Or if you'd prefer to learn by simply having the notes to play highlighted on the virtual keyboard, there's that too.   You  can set all tracks to piano, selectively hide or mute individual tracks, combine all tracks into two tracks (left and right hand), override the default time signature, and transpose the key.  Future improvements should include: ability to combine individual tracks, ability to touch anywhere on the track and either play from there or play just that note/chord, ability to set playback speed as part of the track properties so it is remembered.

title: Nice, but needs saved settings
comment: I finally have a way to listen to my extensive collection of VGM MIDIs. However, the app could use some upgrades:  1) Settings that can be saved / customizable presets for different use cases.  2) A "Set all to piano" button like the desktop version has.  3) Auto-muting of the Percussion tracks, like the desktop versions have.  4) The ability to save the changed MIDI file back to the device/SD card as a new file so I don't have to change the song every time I load it (the OS X version has a workaround for that).  5) Proper detection of tempo or time key changes within a single song. I have several files that do both, and this app (desktop versions included) play those songs at the slowest tempo for the entire song, resulting in incorrect playback speed.  6) The ability to speed up the song as well as the current ability to slow it down.
